description: {"blocks":[{"key":"1a0su","text":"This protocol describes a fully-automated PCR cleanup in a 96-well PCR plate format with AMPure XP beads on an Eppendorf epMotion. Multichannel pipetting with the 300 uL and 50 uL pipettes is used. It is designed to use the thermomixer module; however, this can be replaced by modifying the program to mix by pipetting. The bead magnet used in this program is a Alpaqua Low Elution Magnet Plate. We also use Eppendorf twin.tec PCR plates (LoBind, skirted, 150uL).
